                         FLD Shipping and Receiving


                        SHIPPING & RECEIVING SERVICES
   Location: Building 22
   325 Broadway
   Boulder, CO 80305
   Hours of operation: 7:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.
   Telephone: (303) 497-3405
   Staff: Mike Lukacena, Motor Vehicle Operator
   Chet Madej, Motor Vehicle Operator
   Roland Siebold, Materials Handler
   Ray Stewart, Motor Vehicle Operator
   Daily Procedure: Delivery schedules and special services.
   Mail: All incoming mail and express flats are bulk X rayed and then
   turned over to the mail room for delivery. If a client has called us,
   we will pull a flat and hold it for the client to pick up at Bldg. 22.
   Express Freight: After being X-Rayed, all express freight is divided
   into mail room delivery and freight delivery. All flats and small boxes
   (shoe box or smaller) are given to the mail room for delivery. Clients
   are encouraged to notify Shipping/Receiving of incoming priority
   deliveries.
   FedEx Recent issues, changes in delivery procedures and new services
   are discussed in this memo dated 11/07/2001.
   Problem Areas: Obstacles to speedy delivery, solutions to problems,
   FAQ.
   Help Your Packages Arrive on Time: If it is within your power, ensure
   that shippers have an accurate delivery address. This will speed up the
   handling process before delivery.
   Let us know when you are expecting an urgent shipment. Since we have to
   examine every shipping label, we can watch out for your shipment.
   If you are concerned about a package, give us the tracking number, the
   shipper's name, and whose name is listed as the addressee.
   When you call us about an incoming package, we will notify you of its
   arrival.
